<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Some of you know me and some of you do not, but I feel that it is time for me to voice my opinion. I have spent countless hours playing EQ just sitting quietly in the background listening to the conversation and I have to say, I think DC is currently in peril of collapse. We need someone to inject that life saving breath into the guild, and hopefully it will be soon.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp At this point I offer a challenge to all officers of DC, “Make the Guild fun to be a member of Again”. As it stands now we do very few things that would involve the entire guild and encourage participation. You as officers need to come up with a monthly schedule of events that occur in random zones and at different times to accommodate all levels and play times. These events could be used to level lower level members, obtain a wanted item, give pointers and strategy, or just the fun of wiping a lower level zone. Now this would mean that a few officers would get stuck in a zone that they have not even thought about for 20+ levels, but the help and pointers that are provided should encourage participation and teamwork within the guild. Along with these events there should be at least two in game guild meetings each month and a condition of maintaining your membership in the guild would be mandatory participation in at least one of the meetings each month.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp After looking through Guild Magic, and this by all means does not give an accurate picture of the true guild, I find that we have a potential to have at least double the number of 50+ characters that we currently have. This is only using the main characters that are listed on Guild Magic, when you figure in all of the alts and unlisted characters the possibilities grow substantially. The number of main’s listed as of 9/11/02 would be 33 with an average level of 41, that would be just about where I fall as far as level goes. Now I know that my personal goal is to get to at least 46 by Planes of Power, but I would also like to hit the 50+ mark were I feel I can be a greater use to the guild. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The culmination of what I am saying is “United we stand Divided we fall” and from what I have seen in game and read on the board we a falling at an ever increasing rate. We have high levels leaving, low levels leaving, mid levels leaving, hell everyone is thinking of leaving. The point being in a guild is to be able to get together with friends and have fun the perk is sometimes you get good loot. A perfect example of what I have been saying would be an adventure last weekend involving Chiptooth, Statictooth, Wildbeartooth, Tiggress, and myself. All of the group are RL friends, all of us started EQ at around the same time, and we all came to DC at around the same time. All of this being said, we had however not done anything as a group for a long time, and after a short discussion we had all agreed to go to Sol B even though some of the group would not be getting XP. After a while we moved to Sol A trying to obtain a pair of Impskin Gloves, but it never happened. Even though a couple people died and lost xp we all had a good time and I personally went to two zones I had previously not been to. This short adventure made me feel better about EQ, the people I play with, and the guild that I am in.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Now some if not all of you will or are saying who are you and what gives you the right to criticize the workings of the guild. First and foremost I am a member of DC so that in and of itself gives me the right to criticize and questions everything that happens with the guild. I would however also be one of the people that has lead to the guild making it to the current state it is in. I have done this by setting back and not participating in the various events that have happened in the guild. That is were you as leaders of the guild come into play, you have to make me and all others want to remain in and participate in the guild by arranging the aforementioned events and requiring participation. At first this is going to be a very painstaking task but once we have reestablished ourselves as a guild that is fun and event filled, people will come back and they will bring with them friends.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp It is now crunch time, Do or Die. The things that happen over the next few weeks will set the fate of DC forever. We have to remember membership in the guild should be a privilege not a right, step up or get out. “That is all I have to Say about that”, it is now up to you as leaders to make us the great guild I know we really are, please choose your next moves wisely…<br>
<br>
First and foremost a Toothclan member, and DC member,<br>
Invidious 40th lvl Enchanter<br>
Elroytooth 24th lvl Mage<br>
Nimiety 29th lvl Warrior<br>
