First, I and most, if not all, of the officers have tried to organize events, time and time again, only to have minimal outcome, if anyone shows up at all. The reason for this is that only a small percentage of our members visits the boards, making it very difficult to get information out to the guildmembers. While the guild MOTD works well in theory, it has its limitations, as there's only so much information that can get put up, and it almost constantly gets overwritten.<br>
Second, I don't beleive that it should fall to just the officers to 'get the ball rolling'. DC is a guild with full participation, or should be, meaning that if you want to raid somewhere, or hold an event, and you're not an officer, YOU CAN. If you need a hand organizing it, then come to the officers, and we'll help out. Placing all of the responsibility for organizing events on the officers is unfair, both to the officers, and the other members of DC. <br>
