<br>
I would like to expand on a few points I feel are of the upmost importance. I think a couple other things from the officer section need to be transfered to here also so here it goes....<br>
<br>
1: Reruting. I think some of the officers have been a little scared after the inceidents with Smahinn and have opted to almost discourage recruiting. This was not intentional but I know I started being very leary of the process and would never for any reason invite without a sponsor.....<br>
<br>
     1 way to fix this is to invite one of our lower level (no high MAIN) members to become an officer. This will give us the much needed presence at the lower level that we need. I would also like to have at least 1 day a month each officer spend hanging with some of lower levels as a buff station or guard, poorter what ever yoru class brings. This will do a lot things that as officers we have discussed for a while and this one thing could help start a &quot;mending&quot; process of the guild. I can tell you that the majority of the people you see in the 50 area of DC are from 1 person... Dougy! and were all found in our early 30's late 20's and mostly in SOUTH KARANA!!!!! We need someone willing to get to know people and to be an Ambasador on the low level scene for DC....<br>
<br>
2: Officer participation. Taklinn said part of this the best and I dont want to beat a dead horse but I do want to add something. For you lower level people that have never made it to the high end game...... <br>
You may never know the pain and sweat that goes in to every action.... <br>
To be able to lose 3 days worth of work in 5 min on a simple run through a zone. A blue at 30 is minoote compared to a blue at 52 or 53 or 54.... <br>
When you reach the level that an EPIC! weapon is attainable you will want it too.... <br>
and when you get to the point that it takes 60 min just to get to the zone you can get XP at only to find that 2 hours later you fianlly get a group you too will miss some guild say and some tells..... ( that was for the toothclan that says I ignore them :-(....<br>
and finally when you get to where you are known and people like you and your raiding style and send you a tell that they NEED you for a crazy raid you too will go and you too will get stuck deep in some hole in norrath with mobs surrounding you and then that will be the time the guild needs you and you will miss the call and feel horrible and hope that the guild understands....<br>
<br>
    My point is when I was coming up I never saw Taklinn. I knew he was a good guy from talking to him but I didnt know he was a dwarf until i was 44. I was in the guild at level 25 and for 15 levels I never actually saw taklinn. that doesnt mean that taklinn wasnt working his ass for the guild but it does mean that we never crossed paths for a while until I was able to start joining him on his adventures. It is a fact of life and every officer and high level member of DC went through it BUT&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
    As officers of DC it is our job to be available sometimes. It is our job to spend time making the GUILD stronger not just ourselves. It is our job to support our members and if that means missing a raid to do it well dont say yes when the littler box pops on the screen.... <br>
<br>
    As members of DC you have the same responsibilties of kindness towards others and wearing the DC tag well as the officers. However you also have the responsibility to support us also. Sometimes that means showing up when we call a event and sometimes that means taking on a leadership role and organizing 1 yourselves. <br>
<br>
that last section is kinda hard to understand. I do FULLY believe that this issue is the fault of the officers and leaders of DC. dont take it the wrong way i just need to know that someone actually put here what it feels like to be the highest levels in a guild, just becasue im 52 doesnt mean the adventure is over and im tierd of being a wizard... on the contrary anything else is a complete let down to me....I am Chiptooth <br>
<br>
NOTE: SEE RRAWRR FOR MY THEORY ON MAINS AND HOW YOUR MAIN IS YOUR MAIN FOR A REASON... *wink...<br>
<br>
3: Meetings. This has been thrown around by the officers for a while we started having officer meetings. We thought that was enough. We were wrong. It is time for everyone to make there voice heard to all. For everyone to step up and be a part of the future of DC or ride the wave we create ot et off it PERIOD. It is my opinion that meetings should be mandatory and that the guild Leader be it Myself Dark Bigi Rrawrr Roarry Syn or any one else that has been nominated will have a responsibility to deal with anyone that does not feel that participating in these meeting is important. <br>
<br>
    There are several options for this and I will be discussing these options with the officers. Nothing is to big of a download and anyting can be used in this age of technology. It might be in game, it might be MSN messenger. Options are there we will need to decide on one. If it is ingame I think it will need to be done in 1 zone that is easily acessible by all and ports will have to be done. this needs to be taken seriously..... <br>
<br>
4: High levels leaving DC. I do not in any way think that Saladim, Deshaed or Trackerwolff left for &quot;greener pasteures&quot;. this has been thrown around for all them by different peolple and I truely believe that regardless of where they end up there intention was not to desert us.... However all 3 were officers of this guild and that unfortunetly will not due... It is my opinion that anyone not willing to sign on the dotted line so to speak and stay with us should give up their shield as an officer now before more hurt is done. (that may be a little bit out of my place to say but it is how I feel and that doesnt mean that I will hold it against you but we need to know who is goign to be here 3 months from now and who isnt)....<br>
<br>
    There is no way to fix this. Only power strength and a precense on the high level scene will keep most from leaving. We do  not provide that and this is the reason we have a hard time keping our high level members. At some point they spend more time not doing anything productive and then they have no choice but to move on to a better place to grow (not necesarliy a better place). The high level members of DC have been attempting to change this. We are  few in numbers and as the story goes we dwindle by the day..  We are doing our best though, please forgive us if we spend a little too much time trying to keep our high level friends from falling in the uber hole and only seeing them on a different tag and being drug away by the manaburnign wizzies to stand in front of gornaire till manaburn finishes him off.....<br>
<br>
5: Official discontinuation of bid to join the TGA. This may upset the rest of the officers we spent a long time talking this over and even longer time vieing for a possition in the race while on raids for other people for the past 7 weeks or so. But I think it is now completly apparent that this is destrying DC. If we were getting in to the TGA we would be in it already and then what? With the requirment for attendance I think they have and the posssibility that we could oursleves request help from them and make our own targets what then for the rest of DC. The TGA at this time will only hurt DC. I think its time to think about the family we have and not the friends we would like to have.....<br>
<br>
6: People need to be on the message boards.<br>
<br>
What can I say the horse is beat to death on this already and i am goin to kick it one more time. I am open for suggestions on this.<br>
<br>
<br>
All in all I hope everyone takes from this.........<br>
 <br>
That being a high level in DC is work most of the time. <br>
We made a decision to join TGA that I think has spurred some of the crtisizm that we are getting from with in. <br>
We as officers of DC have abandoned our posts at times. <br>
The members of DC have a responsibility to be strong in our absence. <br>
We need to rebuild from within.<br>
We need to choose a low level and possibly reinstate Taklinn as a high level ambasador for the guild.<br>
We need to comunicate on a regular basis and a standard for attendence to these meetings must be made.<br>
<br>
I hope I am still in the good graces of the Guild I call family<br>
